OL,3,CPostmistress whose life was nearly
OL,4,Cruined by Horizon returns to Post
OL,5,COffice
OL,7,FOn her first day back behind the Post
OL,8,FOffice counter, she said: "There'll
OL,9,Falways be that hurt in the back of the
OL,10,Fmind, the fact that it's happened and
OL,11,Fit's a bad thing, but it's a fresh
OL,12,Fstart now.
OL,14,F"I'm looking forward to having a bit
OL,15,Fof a routine again and getting back in
OL,16,Fthere and serving my community."
OL,18,FChair of the Post Office Nigel Railton
OL,19,Fwas there to see Roopie retake her
OL,20,Fpost, and said the day should mark a
OL,21,Fnew chapter in the company's story.
